-- Germany’s Schaeuble Says 53.5% ‘Haircut’ Proposed for Greek Bond Investors
-- B y   R a i n e r   B u e r g i n
-- 2012-02-21T04:43:36Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-21/germany-s-schaeuble-says-53-5-haircut-proposed-for-greek-bond-investors.html
German Finance Minister  Wolfgang Schaeuble  said euro region ministers at a meeting in Brussels
have proposed a “haircut” of 53.5 percent for private
investors holding Greek government bonds.  Interest rates on the new bonds will start at around 2
percent and rise to as high as 4.3 percent after 2020, Schaeuble
told reporters in Brussels.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Rainer Buergin at 
 rbuergin1@bloomberg.net  